{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"Kurt Andersen: Like many architects, David is a hog for the limelight"},{"time":5000,"text":"but is sufficiently reticent -- or at least pretends to be --"},{"time":8000,"text":"that he asked me to question him rather than speaking."},{"time":13000,"text":"In fact what we're going to talk about,"},{"time":15000,"text":"I think, is in fact a subject that is probably better served"},{"time":23000,"text":"by a conversation than an address."},{"time":24000,"text":"And I guess we have a bit of news clip to precede."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33000,"text":"Dan Rather: Since the September 11th attack on the World Trade Center,"},{"time":37000,"text":"many people have flocked to downtown New York to see"},{"time":39000,"text":"and pay respects at what amounts to the 16-acre burial ground."},{"time":44000,"text":"Now, as CBS's Jim Axelrod reports, they're putting the finishing touches"},{"time":48000,"text":"on a new way for people to visit and view the scene."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"Jim Axelrod: Forget the Empire State Building or the Statue of Liberty."},{"time":55000,"text":"There's a new place in New York"},{"time":57000,"text":"where the crowds are thickest -- Ground Zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"Tourist: I've taken my step-daughter here from Indianapolis."},{"time":63000,"text":"This was -- out of all the tourist sites in New York City --"},{"time":67000,"text":"this was her number-one pick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"JA: Thousands now line up on lower Broadway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"Tourist: I've been wanting to come down here since this happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76000,"text":"JA: Even on the coldest winter days."},{"time":78000,"text":"To honor and remember."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"Tourist: It's reality, it's us. It happened here."},{"time":83000,"text":"This is ours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"JA: So many, in fact, that seeing has become"},{"time":88000,"text":"a bit of a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"Tourist: I think that people are very frustrated"},{"time":91000,"text":"that they're not able to get closer to see what's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"JA: But that is about to change."},{"time":96000,"text":"In record time,"},{"time":98000,"text":"a team of architects and construction workers"},{"time":100000,"text":"designed and built a viewing platform to ease the frustration"},{"time":106000,"text":"and bring people closer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107000,"text":"Man: They'll get an incredible panorama"},{"time":110000,"text":"and understand, I think more completely,"},{"time":112000,"text":"the sheer totality of the destruction of the place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117000,"text":"JA: If you think about it, Ground Zero is unlike"},{"time":119000,"text":"most any other tourist site in America."},{"time":121000,"text":"Unlike the Grand Canyon or the Washington Monument,"},{"time":124000,"text":"people come here to see what's no longer there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"David Rockwell: The first experience people will have here"},{"time":131000,"text":"when they see this is not as a construction site"},{"time":133000,"text":"but as this incredibly moving burial ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136000,"text":"JA: The walls are bare by design, so people can fill them"},{"time":139000,"text":"with their own memorials the way they already have"},{"time":142000,"text":"along the current perimeter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"Tourist: From our hearts, it affected us just as much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"JA: The ramps are made of simple material --"},{"time":149000,"text":"the kind of plywood you see at construction sites --"},{"time":151000,"text":"which is really the whole point."},{"time":153000,"text":"In the face of America's worst destruction"},{"time":156000,"text":"people are building again."},{"time":159000,"text":"Jim Axelrod, CBS News, New York."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162000,"text":"KA: This is not an obvious subject to be in the sensuality segment,"},{"time":167000,"text":"but certainly David you are known as -- I know, a phrase you hate --"},{"time":173000,"text":"an entertainment architect."},{"time":175000,"text":"Your work is highly sensual, even hedonistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"DR: I like that word."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"KA: It's about pleasure -- casinos and hotels and restaurants."},{"time":190000,"text":"How did the shock that all of us -- and especially all of us in New York --"},{"time":193000,"text":"felt on the 11th of September transmute"},{"time":198000,"text":"into your desire to do this thing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"DR: Well the truth of the matter is, post-September 11th,"},{"time":206000,"text":"I felt myself in the role originally --"},{"time":208000,"text":"first of all as someone who lives in Tribeca"},{"time":211000,"text":"and whose neighborhood was devastated,"},{"time":215000,"text":"and as someone who works less than a mile from there --"},{"time":218000,"text":"that I was in the role of forcing 100 people who work with me"},{"time":224000,"text":"in my firm, to continue to have the same level of enthusiasm"},{"time":228000,"text":"about creating the places we had been creating."},{"time":230000,"text":"In fact we're finishing a book which is called \"Pleasure,\""},{"time":234000,"text":"which is about sensual pleasure in spaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"But I've got to tell you -- it became impossible to do that."},{"time":240000,"text":"We were really paralyzed."},{"time":242000,"text":"And I found myself the Friday after September 11th --"},{"time":246000,"text":"two days afterwards --"},{"time":248000,"text":"literally unable to motivate anyone to do anything."},{"time":251000,"text":"We gave the office a few days off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254000,"text":"And in discussing this with other architects,"},{"time":258000,"text":"we had seen people saying in the press"},{"time":263000,"text":"that they should rebuild the towers as they were --"},{"time":266000,"text":"they should rebuild them 50 stories taller."},{"time":269000,"text":"And I thought it was astonishing to speculate,"},{"time":272000,"text":"as if this were a competition,"},{"time":274000,"text":"on something that was such a fresh wound."},{"time":276000,"text":"And I had a series of discussions --"},{"time":280000,"text":"first with Rick Scofidio and Liz Diller, who collaborated with us on this,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and several other people --"},{"time":287000,"text":"and really felt like we had to find relevance in doing something."},{"time":291000,"text":"And that as people who create places, the ultimate way to help"},{"time":297000,"text":"wasn't to pontificate or to make up scenarios,"},{"time":301000,"text":"but to help right now."},{"time":303000,"text":"So we tried to come up with a way,"},{"time":305000,"text":"as a group, to have a kind of design SWAT team."},{"time":307000,"text":"And that was the mission that we came up with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"KA: Were you conscious of suddenly --"},{"time":313000,"text":"as a designer whose work is all about fulfilling wants --"},{"time":318000,"text":"suddenly fulfilling needs?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"DR: Well what I was aware of was,"},{"time":325000,"text":"there was this overwhelming need to act now."},{"time":327000,"text":"And we were asked to participate in a few projects before this."},{"time":336000,"text":"There was a school, PS 234, that had been evacuated down at Ground Zero."},{"time":341000,"text":"They moved to an abandoned school."},{"time":344000,"text":"We took about 20 or 30 architects and designers and artists,"},{"time":347000,"text":"and over four days -- it was like this urban barn-raising --"},{"time":350000,"text":"to renovate it, and everyone wanted to help."},{"time":352000,"text":"It was just extraordinary."},{"time":354000,"text":"Tom Otterness contributed, Maira Kalman contributed"},{"time":357000,"text":"and it became this cathartic experience for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"KA: And that was done, effectively,"},{"time":363000,"text":"by October 8 or something?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"DR: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"KA: Obviously, what you faced in trying to do something"},{"time":370000,"text":"as substantial as this project -- and this is only one of four"},{"time":373000,"text":"that you've designed to surround the site --"},{"time":376000,"text":"you must have run up against the incredibly byzantine,"},{"time":383000,"text":"entrenched bureaucracy and powers that be"},{"time":388000,"text":"in New York real estate and New York politics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"DR: Well, it's a funny thing."},{"time":392000,"text":"We finished PS 234, and had dinner with a small group."},{"time":395000,"text":"I was actually asked to be a committee chair on an AIA committee to rebuild."},{"time":400000,"text":"And I sat in on several meetings."},{"time":402000,"text":"And there were the most circuitous grand plans"},{"time":406000,"text":"that had to do with long-term infrastructure and rebuilding the entire city."},{"time":411000,"text":"And the fact is that there were immediate wounds and needs that needed to be filled,"},{"time":417000,"text":"and there was talk about inclusion and wanting it to be an inclusive process."},{"time":420000,"text":"And it wasn't an inclusive group."},{"time":422000,"text":"So we said, what is --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"KA: It was not an inclusive group?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"DR: It was not an inclusive group."},{"time":427000,"text":"It was predominantly a white, rich, corporate group"},{"time":430000,"text":"that was not representative of the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"KA: Shocking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436000,"text":"DR: Yeah, surprising."},{"time":438000,"text":"So Rick and Liz and Kevin and I came up with the idea."},{"time":443000,"text":"The city actually approached us."},{"time":447000,"text":"We first approached the city about Pier 94."},{"time":450000,"text":"We saw how PS 234 worked."},{"time":452000,"text":"The families -- the victims of the families --"},{"time":454000,"text":"were going to this pier that was incredibly dehumanizing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"KA: On the Hudson River?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458000,"text":"DR: Yeah. And the city actually -- through Tim Zagat initially,"},{"time":461000,"text":"and then through Christyne Nicholas, then we got to Giuliani --"},{"time":464000,"text":"said, \"You know we don't want to do anything with Pier 94 right now,"},{"time":467000,"text":"but we have an observation platform for the families down at Ground Zero"},{"time":470000,"text":"that we'd like to be a more dignified experience for the families,"},{"time":474000,"text":"and a way to protect it from the weather.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"So I went down there with Rick and Liz and Kevin,"},{"time":480000,"text":"and I've got to say, it was the most moving experience of my life."},{"time":485000,"text":"It was devastating to see the simple plywood platform with a rail around it,"},{"time":489000,"text":"where the families of the victims had left notes to them."},{"time":492000,"text":"And there was no mediation between us and the experience."},{"time":496000,"text":"There was no filter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"And I remembered on September 11th, on 14th Street,"},{"time":503000,"text":"the roof of our building -- we can see the World Trade Towers prominently --"},{"time":506000,"text":"and I saw the first building collapse from a conference room"},{"time":513000,"text":"on the eighth floor on a TV that we had set up."},{"time":515000,"text":"And then everyone was up on the roof, so I ran up there."},{"time":519000,"text":"And it was amazing how much harder it was"},{"time":522000,"text":"to believe in real life than it was on TV."},{"time":525000,"text":"There was something about the comfort of the filter"},{"time":527000,"text":"and how much information was between us and the experience."},{"time":530000,"text":"So seeing this in a very simple,"},{"time":532000,"text":"dignified way was a very powerful experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536000,"text":"So we went back to the city and said"},{"time":538000,"text":"we're not particularly interested in the upgrade of this as a VIP platform,"},{"time":541000,"text":"but we've spent some time down there."},{"time":546000,"text":"At the same time the city had this need."},{"time":551000,"text":"They were looking for a solution"},{"time":553000,"text":"to deal with 30 or 40 thousand people a day"},{"time":555000,"text":"who were going down there, that had nowhere to go."},{"time":558000,"text":"And there was no way to deal with the traffic around the site."},{"time":561000,"text":"So dealing with it is just an immediate master plan."},{"time":563000,"text":"There was a way -- there had to be a way --"},{"time":565000,"text":"to get people to move around the site."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568000,"text":"KA: But then you've got to figure out a way --"},{"time":571000,"text":"we will skip over the insanely tedious process of getting permits"},{"time":576000,"text":"and getting everybody on board -- but simply funding this thing."},{"time":579000,"text":"It looks like a fairly simple thing,"},{"time":582000,"text":"but this was a half a million dollar project?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"DR: Well, we knew that if it wasn't privately funded,"},{"time":586000,"text":"it wasn't going to happen."},{"time":588000,"text":"And we also, frankly, knew that if it didn't happen"},{"time":590000,"text":"by the end of the Giuliani administration,"},{"time":592000,"text":"then everyone who we were dealing with at the DOT"},{"time":594000,"text":"and the Police Department and all of the --"},{"time":597000,"text":"we were meeting with 20 or 30 people with the city at a time,"},{"time":601000,"text":"and it was set up by the Office of Emergency Management."},{"time":604000,"text":"This incredible act on their part, because they really wanted this,"},{"time":608000,"text":"and they sensed that this needed to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610000,"text":"KA: And there was therefore this ticking clock,"},{"time":613000,"text":"because Giuliani was obviously out three months after that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"DR: Yeah. So the first thing we had to do was find a way to get this --"},{"time":621000,"text":"we had to work with the families of the victims,"},{"time":625000,"text":"through the city, to make sure that they knew this was happening."},{"time":628000,"text":"Because this didn't want to be a surprise."},{"time":630000,"text":"And we also had to be as under the radar screen as we could be in New York,"},{"time":634000,"text":"because the key was not raising a lot of objection"},{"time":637000,"text":"and sort of working as quietly as possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"We came up with the idea of setting up a foundation,"},{"time":645000,"text":"mainly because when we found a contractor who would build this,"},{"time":650000,"text":"he would not agree to do this, even if we would pay him the money."},{"time":656000,"text":"There needed to be a foundation in place."},{"time":657000,"text":"So we came up with a foundation, and actually what happened was"},{"time":662000,"text":"one major developer in New York --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"KA: Who shall remain nameless, I guess?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"DR: Yeah. His initials are JS, and he owns Rockefeller Center,"},{"time":669000,"text":"if that helps anyone -- volunteered to help."},{"time":673000,"text":"And we met with him."},{"time":675000,"text":"The prices from the contractors were between five to 700,000 dollars."},{"time":681000,"text":"And Atlantic-Heydt, who's the largest scaffolding contractor in the country,"},{"time":684000,"text":"volunteered to do it at cost."},{"time":688000,"text":"So this developer said, \"You know what, we'll underwrite the entire expense.\""},{"time":691000,"text":"And we said, \"That's incredible!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":694000,"text":"And I think this was the 21st,"},{"time":696000,"text":"and we knew this had to be built and up by the 28th."},{"time":698000,"text":"And we had to start construction the next day."},{"time":702000,"text":"We had a meeting that evening with his contractor of choice,"},{"time":706000,"text":"and the contractor showed up with the drawings of the platform"},{"time":710000,"text":"about half the size that we had drawn it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712000,"text":"KA: Sort of like the Spinal Tap scene where you get"},{"time":714000,"text":"the tiny little Stonehenge, I guess?"},{"time":716000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":720000,"text":"DR: In fact, it was as if this was going to be window-washing scaffolding."},{"time":723000,"text":"There was no sense of the fact that this is next to Saint Paul --"},{"time":727000,"text":"that this is really a place that needs to be kind of dignified,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and a place to reflect and remember."},{"time":733000,"text":"And I've got to say that we spent a lot of time"},{"time":736000,"text":"in putting this together, watching the crowds that gathered at Saint Paul --"},{"time":739000,"text":"which is just to the right -- and moving around the site."},{"time":741000,"text":"And I live down there, so we spent a lot of time looking at the need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"And I think people were amazed at two things --"},{"time":749000,"text":"I think they were amazed at the destruction,"},{"time":751000,"text":"but I think there was a sense of disbelief"},{"time":754000,"text":"about the heroics of New Yorkers that I found very moving."},{"time":758000,"text":"Just the sort of everyday heroics of New Yorkers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761000,"text":"So we were in this meeting and the contractor literally said,"},{"time":766000,"text":"\"I'm going to lock the door, because this developer"},{"time":768000,"text":"will not agree to have you leave till you've signed off on this.\""},{"time":772000,"text":"And we said, \"Well, this is half the size,"},{"time":774000,"text":"it doesn't have any of the design features"},{"time":778000,"text":"that have been agreed upon by everyone -- everyone in the city."},{"time":780000,"text":"We'd have to go back to the beginning to do this.\""},{"time":784000,"text":"And I convinced him that we should leave the room"},{"time":787000,"text":"with the agreement to build it as designed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"The next day I got an email from the developer"},{"time":794000,"text":"saying that he was withdrawing all funding."},{"time":798000,"text":"So we didn't know what to do,"},{"time":802000,"text":"but we decided to cast a very wide net."},{"time":804000,"text":"We emailed out letters to as many people as we could --"},{"time":807000,"text":"several people in the audience here -- who were very helpful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811000,"text":"KA: There was no thought of abandoning ship at that point?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"DR: No. In fact I told the contractor to go ahead."},{"time":818000,"text":"He had already ordered materials based on my go-ahead."},{"time":820000,"text":"We knew that one way or another this was going to happen."},{"time":823000,"text":"And we just felt it had to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"KA: You were funding it yourself and with contributions and this foundation."},{"time":834000,"text":"Richard, I think very correctly,"},{"time":839000,"text":"made the point at the beginning --"},{"time":841000,"text":"before all the chair designers came out --"},{"time":845000,"text":"about the history of chair designers imposing aesthetic solutions"},{"time":850000,"text":"on this kind of universal, banal, common problem of sitting."},{"time":854000,"text":"It seems to me with this,"},{"time":858000,"text":"that it was the opposite of that."},{"time":860000,"text":"This was an unprecedented, singular design problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"DR: Well here's the issue:"},{"time":866000,"text":"we knew that this was not in the sense of --"},{"time":869000,"text":"we think about the site, and think about the need for a memorial."},{"time":877000,"text":"It was important that this not be categorized as a memorial."},{"time":878000,"text":"That this was a place for people to reflect, to remember --"},{"time":884000,"text":"a kind of quiet place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"So it led us to using design solutions"},{"time":891000,"text":"that created as few filters between the viewer --"},{"time":894000,"text":"as we said about the families' platform -- and the experience as possible."},{"time":897000,"text":"It's all incredibly humble material."},{"time":900000,"text":"It's scaffolding and plywood."},{"time":904000,"text":"And it allows -- by sort of the procession of the movement,"},{"time":908000,"text":"up by Saint Paul's and down the other side --"},{"time":911000,"text":"it gives you about 300 feet to go up 13 feet from the ground"},{"time":915000,"text":"to where you get the 360 degree view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":918000,"text":"But the design was driven by a need to be quick, cheap, safe, respectful, flexible."},{"time":926000,"text":"One of the other things is this is designed to be moveable."},{"time":929000,"text":"Because when we looked at the four platforms around the site,"},{"time":933000,"text":"one of which is an upgrade of the families' platform,"},{"time":936000,"text":"we knew that these had to be moveable"},{"time":938000,"text":"to respond to changing conditions,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and the changing definition of what Ground Zero is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946000,"text":"KA: Your work -- I mean, we've talked about this before --"},{"time":949000,"text":"a lot of your work, I think, is informed by your belief in, or your focus on"},{"time":955000,"text":"the temporariness of all things and the evanescence of things,"},{"time":959000,"text":"and a kind of \"Eat, drink, and be merry, for tomorrow we die,\""},{"time":963000,"text":"sort of sense of existence."},{"time":966000,"text":"This is clearly not a work for the ages."},{"time":972000,"text":"You know, a couple of years this thing isn't going to be here."},{"time":976000,"text":"Did that require, as an architect,"},{"time":979000,"text":"a new way of thinking about what you were doing?"},{"time":981000,"text":"To think of it as this purely temporary installation?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"DR: No, I don't think so."},{"time":987000,"text":"I think this is, obviously, substantially different"},{"time":991000,"text":"from anything we'd ever thought about doing before, just by the nature of it."},{"time":996000,"text":"Where it overlaps with thoughts about our work in general is,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"number one -- the notion of collaboration as a sort of way to get things done."},{"time":1005000,"text":"And Kevin Kennon, Rick Scofidio, Liz Diller"},{"time":1010000,"text":"and all the people within the city --"},{"time":1015000,"text":"Norman Lear, who I spoke to four hours before our deadline for funding,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"offered to give us a bridge loan to help us get through it."},{"time":1024000,"text":"So the notion of collaboration --"},{"time":1026000,"text":"I think this reinforces how important that is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"And in terms of the temporary nature of it,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"our goal was not to create something"},{"time":1035000,"text":"that would be there longer than it needed to be."},{"time":1038000,"text":"I think what we were most interested in was promoting a kind of dialogue"},{"time":1043000,"text":"that we felt may not have been happening enough in this city,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"about what's really happening there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050000,"text":"And a day or two before it opened was Giuliani's farewell address,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"where he proposed the idea of all of Ground Zero being a memorial."},{"time":1059000,"text":"Which was very controversial, but it resonated with a lot of people."},{"time":1062000,"text":"And I think regardless of what the position is about how"},{"time":1067000,"text":"this sacred piece of land is to be used,"},{"time":1071000,"text":"having it come out of actually seeing it in a real encounter,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"I think makes it a more powerful dialogue."},{"time":1078000,"text":"And that's what we were interested in."},{"time":1080000,"text":"So that, very much, is in the realm of things"},{"time":1083000,"text":"I've been interested in before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085000,"text":"KA: It seems to me, among other things, a lovely piece of civic infrastructure."},{"time":1088000,"text":"It enables that conversation to get serious."},{"time":1092000,"text":"And six months after the fact --"},{"time":1095000,"text":"and only a few months away from the site being cleaned --"},{"time":1099000,"text":"we are very quickly, now, getting to the point"},{"time":1101000,"text":"where those conversations about what should go there are getting serious."},{"time":1106000,"text":"Do you have -- having been as physically involved in the site"},{"time":1111000,"text":"as you have been doing this project -- have any ideas about"},{"time":1113000,"text":"what should or shouldn't be done?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115000,"text":"DR: Well, I think one thing that shouldn't be done is evaluate --"},{"time":1120000,"text":"I think right now the discussion is a very closed discussion on the master plan."},{"time":1126000,"text":"The Protetch Gallery recently had a show on ideas for buildings,"},{"time":1131000,"text":"which had some sort of inventive ideas of buildings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1135000,"text":"KA: But it had some really terrible ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1137000,"text":"DR: And it also felt a little bit like a kind of competition of ideas,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"where I think the focus of ideas should be on master planning and uses."},{"time":1146000,"text":"And I think there should be a broader -- which there's starting to be --"},{"time":1149000,"text":"the dialogue is really opening up to,"},{"time":1151000,"text":"what does this site really want to be?"},{"time":1153000,"text":"And I truly believe until the issue of memorial is sorted out,"},{"time":1157000,"text":"that it's going to be very hard to have an intelligent discussion."},{"time":1160000,"text":"There's a few discussions right now that I think are very positive,"},{"time":1165000,"text":"about depressing the West Side Highway and connecting this over,"},{"time":1169000,"text":"so that there's one uninterrupted piece of land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172000,"text":"KA: Well, I think that's interesting."},{"time":1174000,"text":"And it gets to another issue that was probably inappropriate"},{"time":1177000,"text":"to discuss six months ago, but perhaps isn't now,"},{"time":1179000,"text":"which is, not many of us love the World Trade Center as a piece of architecture,"},{"time":1185000,"text":"as what it had done to this city and that huge plaza."},{"time":1189000,"text":"Is this an opportunity, is the silver lining --"},{"time":1192000,"text":"a silver lining, here -- to rebuild"},{"time":1194000,"text":"some more traditional city grid, or not?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1198000,"text":"DR: I think there's a real opportunity to engage"},{"time":1200000,"text":"in a discussion of why we live in cities."},{"time":1202000,"text":"And why do we live in places where such dissimilar people"},{"time":1206000,"text":"collide up against us each day?"},{"time":1208000,"text":"I don't think it has much to do with 50 or 60 or 70 or 80 thousand new office spaces,"},{"time":1213000,"text":"regardless of what the number is."},{"time":1215000,"text":"So yeah, I think there is a chance to re-look at how we think about cities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1219000,"text":"And in fact, there's a proposal on the table now for building number seven."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1225000,"text":"KA: Which was the building just north of the Towers?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1227000,"text":"DR: Right, which the towers fell into."},{"time":1229000,"text":"And the reason that's been held up is essentially by community outrage"},{"time":1234000,"text":"that they're not re-opening the street"},{"time":1236000,"text":"to connect that back to the rest of the city."},{"time":1238000,"text":"I think a public dialogue -- I think, you know,"},{"time":1241000,"text":"I'd like to see an international competition,"},{"time":1245000,"text":"and a call for ideas for uses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1248000,"text":"KA: Whether it's arts, whether it's housing,"},{"time":1250000,"text":"whether it's what amount of shopping?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1252000,"text":"DR: Right. And we're looking for other things."},{"time":1254000,"text":"This small foundation we put together is looking for other ways to help."},{"time":1257000,"text":"Including taking a small piece adjacent to the site"},{"time":1261000,"text":"and inviting 10 architects who currently don't have a voice"},{"time":1265000,"text":"in New York to do artist housing."},{"time":1267000,"text":"And find other ways to encourage the discussion"},{"time":1269000,"text":"to be against sort of monolithic, single solutions,"},{"time":1272000,"text":"and more about a multiplicity of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1276000,"text":"KA: Before we end, I know you have a piece of digital video"},{"time":1283000,"text":"of the experience of being on this platform?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1286000,"text":"DR: John Kamen -- who's here, actually -- put together"},{"time":1289000,"text":"a two and a half minute piece that shows the platform in use."},{"time":1292000,"text":"So I thought that would be good to end with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1307000,"text":"DR: We're looking from Fulton Street, west."},{"time":1313000,"text":"One of the tricky issues we had with the Giuliani administration"},{"time":1317000,"text":"was I had forgotten how anti-graffiti he was."},{"time":1320000,"text":"And essentially our structure was designed to be written on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1327000,"text":"KA: As you say, it's not a memorial."},{"time":1329000,"text":"But were you conscious of memorials? The Vietnam Memorial?"},{"time":1331000,"text":"Those kinds of forms?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1333000,"text":"DR: We certainly did as much research as we could,"},{"time":1338000,"text":"and we were conscious of other memorials."},{"time":1342000,"text":"And also the complexity and length of time they really take to do."},{"time":1345000,"text":"It's 350 people on the committee for Oklahoma City,"},{"time":1349000,"text":"which is why we thought of this as a sort of ad-hoc, spontaneous solution"},{"time":1354000,"text":"that expanded on Union Square"},{"time":1357000,"text":"and the places that were ad-hoc memorials in the city already."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1365000,"text":"The scaffolding you can see built up over the street is de-mountable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1381000,"text":"What's interesting now is the nature of the site has totally changed,"},{"time":1385000,"text":"so that what you're aware of"},{"time":1387000,"text":"is not just the destruction of the buildings in Ground Zero,"},{"time":1392000,"text":"but all of the buildings around it --"},{"time":1394000,"text":"and the scars on the building around it, which are enormous."},{"time":1397000,"text":"This shows Saint Paul's on the left."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1406000,"text":"KA: I just want to thank you on behalf of New Yorkers"},{"time":1411000,"text":"for making this happen and getting this done."},{"time":1414000,"text":"But the kind of virtually instantaneous nature of its erection,"},{"time":1419000,"text":"and its being there,"},{"time":1422000,"text":"almost before you could believe"},{"time":1425000,"text":"that a response of this magnitude could be accomplished,"},{"time":1429000,"text":"is part of its extraordinary --"},{"time":1434000,"text":"I don't know if beauty is the word --"},{"time":1437000,"text":"but presence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1440000,"text":"DR: It was an honor to do."},{"time":1442000,"text":"And we were thrilled to be able to show it here."}]}]}